## Header 1

```{r setup}
library(tidyverse)
library(here)
library(fs)
source(here("R/functions.R"))
#| include: false
```

##Importing new data 
# Find function: Ctrl + shift + p
#New code block: Ctrl + ALt + i
#New pipe: Cmd + shift m 
#This data is written in pascal case (CollectionDatetime), we change it to snake case, which is where all words are written in lower case with words devided by a underscore (and therefore we added "library(snakecase)" in the code chunk above, and ", name_repair = to_snake_case")
#Insert "Help" section by inserting "?read_csv" in the console. You just use it when you need help, and it therefore should not be a part 
# To get an overview of just a bit of the data, we typed in "n_max = 100", which provides a tibble with max 100 rows
#We delete library(snakecase)
```{r}
#| eval: FALSE
here("data-raw/nurses-stress/stress/5C/5C_1586886626/HR.csv.gz") |>
  readr::read_csv(
    show_col_types = FALSE,
    name_repair = snakecase::to_snake_case,
    n_max = 100
  )
```

